From Phil Burg Subject Re How is a Loopback connector made Shaw Goh writes wrote I need to know the Pins to connect to make a loopback connector for a serial port so I can build one The loopback connector is used to test the serial port Thanks for any help Steve Me Too In a pin serial loopback plug, you need to connect the following pins pin to pin pin to pin pins , and together pins , , and together pins , and together, pin to pin That should do it Note that a lot of these pins are redundant in many implementations Phil Phil Burg Computer Unit, CSIRO Division of Entomology Australia Life a sexually transmitted disease with a mortality rate